-- Alexander Gelber Named Acting Chief Economist at U.S. Treasury
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2013-04-26T19:08:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-26/alexander-gelber-named-acting-chief-economist-at-u-s-treasury.html
U.S. Treasury official Alexander
Gelber has been named acting chief economist, according to a
department spokeswoman.  Gelber, who has been deputy assistant secretary for
economic policy, becomes the acting assistant secretary,
Treasury spokeswoman Sabrina Siddiqui said.  Gelber is on temporary leave from his positions as
assistant professor in the Business Economics and Public Policy
Department at the University of Pennsylvania’s Wharton School
and as faculty research fellow at the National Bureau of
Economic Research.  Janice Eberly, who has been assistant secretary for
economic policy, or chief economist, leaves the department today
to return to her faculty job at Northwestern University’s
Kellogg School of Management.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in  Washington  at 
 ikatz2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
